{
  "stem": "27390.7",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Four and a half years in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I've never given up hope.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To the last minute I was hoping I would get over this.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If one gives up hope, that's the end of it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A bit of each.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, I didn't, we didn't-- if people tell you stories that they managed to pray, everybody prayed in their heart, I suppose.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we didn't have time to pray.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember it was Yom Kippur, Yom Kippur, the Day of Atonement that means in English, which is the most secret-- sacred day in the Jewish calendar.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we-- and the Germans, they knew when the Jewish holidays are.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they specially gave us harder work, and less food, and more beatings in those days.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there were more killings going on in those days than any other day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, my mother and my sister were, were gassed on the first day of Rosh Hashanah.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I know that because I have, I still have three cousins living in Israel, and they were there with my mother.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they know when they were gassed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My sister maybe would have been alive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Also she did the same thing as in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She went with my mother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they were both gassed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And, talking about-- there were some exceptional people that kept-- we were 26 boys, I told you, living in this-- in the-- in the-- in the barrack, in like a, it was called a stube in German, a room with the-- we shared two, two boys to a bunk, well three bunks, one on top of the other.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And these bunks-- in the morning, there was a siren, and we had to jump off the beds.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
